description: Theoretical fees associated with the campaign. The given object should represent the association between theoretical fees and the number of items subject to these fees. For instance, {"1.20": "20", "1.50": "100"} means that 20 items of this campaign were sent with a cost of 1.20 each and 100 items with a cost of 1.50. If the theoretical fee is null or unknown, a empty object can be given or the field can be left out. This field must only be set if the status is set to "sent".
